    "Subsequently, we progress to the annotation phase of active learning, as illustrated in Figure 1 (b).",
    "The customized LLMannotated explanation revision function g (to be discussed in Section 5.3) annotates completions (â, r) for the selected samples in Q n using the LLM T, guided by the completion (a, r) generated by the small model, represented as",
    "For each q ∈ Q n, this results in the dataset D n = {(q i, âi, ri)} m for small model fine-tuning.",
    "The datasets are updated by removing Q n from U and adding D n to the cumulative training set D.",
    "Finally, in the model update phase of active learning, depicted in Figure 1 (c), we fine-tune the small model S on the training set D. This process is repeated until the LLM annotating (labeling) budget Bu is depleted or other stopping criteria are met (e.g., marginal improvement of the small model falls below a certain threshold)."
